Florida Governor Charlie Crist will be introducing President Barack Obama at a town hall meeting in Fort Myers. The meeting will focus on discussing the need for a plan to help American families during the economic downturn and lay the groundwork for long-term recovery. Both President Obama and Governor Crist acknowledge the toll the crisis has taken on the American people and emphasize the importance of providing urgent relief to those in need. Governor Crist also highlights the need for federal stimulus to prioritize job creation and targeted tax relief for small business owners.